result.execSummary:
The defendant Keith John Stepniewski was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Causing a Child to Expose Genitals/Pubic Area/Intimate Parts, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.10(1)(a).
  • Expose Child to Harmful Descriptions, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.11(2)(am).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

superMiscConds.notes: Court orders the fines, costs, and restitution in this file shall be paid from all earnings received in accordance with prison policy, not to exceed 25% of gross during the term of initial confinement. If any fines, costs, and/or restitution remain outstanding at the end of the initial confinement portion of this sentence, then the remaining shall be paid as a condition of extended supervision.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.  Defendant is prohibited from having any contact with females under the age of 18 years, unless contact is approved by the supervising agent and contact is in the presence of a parent or guardian.  Defendant is prohibited from having any contact with S.T.K.

Defendant to comply with the Sex Offender Registration Program - a lifetime registration is required.  Complete a Sex Offender Treatment Assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the Supervising Agent.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

records.addlTxt: Case Called @ 2:14 PM: Defendant Keith John Stepniewski in court with attorney John B. Selsing.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court has received and reviewed PSI.  Counsel admit receipt of same and no factual corrections offered.  Chapter 950 in compliance.   State confirms there has been no receipt of any VIS.  Argument by DA - DOC recommendation is wholly deficient and will argue for deviation from same.  Argument by Atty Selsing - agrees with recommendation for supervision and cond'l time.  Statement by Def:  Yes.   The Court:  As to Ct No 2: 3 -1/2 yr term of imprisonment bifurcated as 18 mos IC/2 yrs ES.  Concurrent to any existing SEH.  As to Ct 3: S/W - 3 yrs probation Consecutive to term of imprisonment on Ct 2.  Net effect for a 6-1/2 yr SEH.  Conditions of ES:  Complete SOT;  Register for SO for life; no contact with females under the age of 18 yrs unless approved by Agent, and in the presence of a parent or guardian; No contact with STK; AODA; the defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician; Court Costs as to each Count plus DNA Surcharge - DNA sample already provided.  Bond revoked for delivery to WCSD and ultimate transport to DCI.  Court has the authority to stay the commencement of prison SEH, but declines to do so.  Further statement by Def for stay for medical reasons.  Court declines request, sentence imposed is necessary in light of  what occurred.  Def not eligible for SAP/CIP.  Appeal Rights Given.
